text: Where is the father of those children? I'm sick of seeing films and TV shows featuring mothers and their children but with no explanation regarding who the father is. It's patronising to the viewer and demeans fatherhood. Also can be have at least a few films featuring women in their 30s and 40s that don't define women according to their role as "someone's mother"? Who is also physically weak? Like those countless films about men going on quests, pursuing their dreams, solving complex scientific or mathematical problems, inventing things, starting political revolutions? The only fun thing about this is the biker gang. Do they get a spin off? THAT is a film I'd see.
